    "text_blocks_bpeLpd": {
      "type": "text-blocks",
      "blocks": {
        "block_iH7LCF": {
          "type": "block",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "none",
            "title": "",
            "text": "<p>PEGGY HARTANTO celebrates the grand opening of its first flagship store at Plaza Senayan, Jakarta, after previously opening its doors to the public last March. This first standalone retail space serves as an important milestone in the Indonesian fashion label’s journey since its establishment in 2012 by sisters Peggy, Petty, and Lydia Hartanto. The event today coincides with the launch of the brand’s new FLORET leather goods collection.<br/><br/>The striking architectural space is rooted in PEGGY HARTANTO’s ethos of elegance and precision, as evident in the strong, structured architectural lines juxtaposed with organic shapes. The interior features a contrasting palette of dark brown and powder blue accentuated with chrome surfaces and structured clay walls, creating a minimalist yet dynamic environment that allows guests to engage with the brand’s ready-to-wear designs with no distractions. </p>",
            "cta_link": "",
            "cta_label": ""
          }
        },
        "block_LWDnXH": {
          "type": "block",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "none",
            "title": "",
            "text": "<p>For the grand opening event, the store has been transformed with the addition of surrealist floral installations, mimicking the motifs found on the new FLORET leather goods design, conceptualized by the Surabaya-based design studio Sciencewerk. To further complement the store’s atmosphere, musician Mariska Setiawan has curated a special playlist as a soulful soundscape for the space (<a href=\"https://open.spotify.com/playlist/4X6VUoZzyMp46tmrtzWMkw?si=_vDK5P7kQ5GmBlQs2huiDw&nd=1&dlsi=819d427a44254200\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">listen on Spotify</span></a>).<br/><br/>“Set against the store’s interior, these unique installations offer a dreamlike ambience that we hope will immerse our guests in the brand’s narrative for the season, where the bold is contrasted with the poetic, the elegant with the imaginative,” says Lydia, the Managing Director of PEGGY HARTANTO.</p>",
            "cta_link": "",
            "cta_label": ""
          }
        }
      },
